{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-page-js","path":"/patterns/general-patterns/graphs-and-when-to-use-them","result":{"data":{"page":{"frontmatter":{"meta":null,"title":"Graphs and when to use them","intro":"Generell information about the graphs and some does and don'ts and when we prefer the usage of the different graphs. ","template":"ArticlePage","category":"General Patterns","background":null,"wide":false,"lang":false,"contentTop":null,"heroBlock":null},"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"how-to-use","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How to use"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#how-to-use","ariaLabel":"how to use permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Graphs are used to visualize data and to help people quickly understand and use information that are too numerous or complicated to be described adequately in the text and in less space. Do not, however, use graphs for small amounts of data that could be conveyed succinctly in a sentence."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Drawing and presenting data visually in graphs, charts, diagrams or even maps are powerful tools which help the user understand and comprehend the data more intuitively. When dealing with shares, funds, money and other more or less \"complicated\" bank matters, visualizing the data is often recommended."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"type-of-graph","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Type of graph"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#type-of-graph","ariaLabel":"type of graph permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There are different kind of graphs to use, here comes some way of thinking wen to use them:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"---a-line-graph","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":". . . a Line Graph"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#---a-line-graph","ariaLabel":"   a line graph permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Line graphs are used to track changes over short and long periods of time. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/line-graph","target":"_target","rel":["external","nofollow","noreferrer","noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"More about line graph"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"---a-pie-chart","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":". . . a Pie Chart."},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#---a-pie-chart","ariaLabel":"   a pie chart permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pie charts are best to use when you are trying to compare parts of a whole. They do not show changes over time."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/piechart","target":"_target","rel":["external","nofollow","noreferrer","noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"More about Pie Chart"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"---a-bar-graph","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":". . . a Bar Graph."},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#---a-bar-graph","ariaLabel":"   a bar graph permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Bar graphs are used to compare things between different groups or to track changes over time. However, bar graphs are best when the changes are larger."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/bar-graph","target":"_target","rel":["external","nofollow","noreferrer","noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"More about Bar Graph"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/distribution-bar","target":"_target","rel":["external","nofollow","noreferrer","noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"More about Distribution bar"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"---an-area-graph","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":". . . an Area Graph."},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#---an-area-graph","ariaLabel":"   an area graph permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Area graphs are very similar to line graphs. They can be used to track changes over time for one or more groups. Use area charts only if you want to show how values develop over time."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/data-visualization/area-graph"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"More about Area Graph"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"---an-x-y-plot","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":". . . an X-Y Plot."},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#---an-x-y-plot","ariaLabel":"   an x y plot permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"X-Y plots are used to determine relationships between the two different things. The x-axis is used to measure one event (or variable) and the y-axis is used to measure the other. If both variables increase at the same time, they have a positive relationship. If one variable decreases while the other increases, they have a negative relationship. Sometimes the variables don't follow any pattern and have no relationship."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"More about X-Y Plot"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"---a-map-chart","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":". . . a Map Chart."},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#---a-map-chart","ariaLabel":"   a map chart permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use a map if you have data with a geographical component. Maps can shade areas in proportion to mapped values, allowing for visual pop-out of high-value areas. Data for map charts must contain geographical names corresponding to the geographical entities represented on the map. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/map","target":"_target","rel":["external","nofollow","noreferrer","noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"More about Map Chart"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"the-different-parts","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The different parts"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#the-different-parts","ariaLabel":"the different parts permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"legends","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Legends"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#legends","ariaLabel":"legends permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Important to each graphical element is a legend describing the visual data. The legends should be 16x16 pixels, with text in Arial that describes the legend."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Position-wise, they should be in close relation to the graph itself. Prefereble on the right or under the graph."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"interactivity","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Interactivity"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#interactivity","ariaLabel":"interactivity permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If the graph/chart has interactivity attached to it. Click on the legends to highlight the different parts in the graph. Even the text of the legend should be clickable."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"color","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Color"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#color","ariaLabel":"color permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"LFUI provides a few scales to choose from that will color your visual data according to the visual profile of Länsförsäkringar. The visual identity set a preferable scale of blue or red. Below we have set different set to make it the same for all graphs. Use colors to make your most important value stand out"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We are going to update the colors for better accessibility. [2019-12-01]"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here are the latest sets of colors to use:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Blue colors - 10 colors"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Red colors - 10 colors"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Blue to red - 16 colors"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Red to blue - 16 colors"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hybrid - 4 colors"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Map - 15 colors"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Disabled / not selected / inactive color is grey #d9d9d9 (smoke)."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{"id":"accessibility","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Accessibility"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#accessibility","ariaLabel":"accessibility permalink","className":["Heading--anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"width":"14","height":"19"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z","fill":"#E5E5E5","fillRule":"nonzero"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Charts, graphs and maps use visuals to convey complex images to users. But since they are images, these media provide serious accessibility issues to colorblind users and users of screen readers. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Generally speaking an ALT tag cannot do justice to a complex chart. One way to describe a chart is to provide both a text summary and a properly coded data table near the chart."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This serves multiple audiences because a chart can show trends, but a table can provide exact data for those who are interested."}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"html":"<h2 id=\"how-to-use\" style=\"position:relative;\">How to use<a href=\"#how-to-use\" aria-label=\"how to use permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Graphs are used to visualize data and to help people quickly understand and use information that are too numerous or complicated to be described adequately in the text and in less space. Do not, however, use graphs for small amounts of data that could be conveyed succinctly in a sentence.</p>\n<p>Drawing and presenting data visually in graphs, charts, diagrams or even maps are powerful tools which help the user understand and comprehend the data more intuitively. When dealing with shares, funds, money and other more or less \"complicated\" bank matters, visualizing the data is often recommended.</p>\n<h3 id=\"type-of-graph\" style=\"position:relative;\">Type of graph<a href=\"#type-of-graph\" aria-label=\"type of graph permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h3>\n<p>There are different kind of graphs to use, here comes some way of thinking wen to use them:</p>\n<h4 id=\"---a-line-graph\" style=\"position:relative;\">. . . a Line Graph<a href=\"#---a-line-graph\" aria-label=\"   a line graph permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>Line graphs are used to track changes over short and long periods of time. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/line-graph\" target=\"_target\" rel=\"external nofollow noreferrer noopener\">More about line graph</a></p>\n<h4 id=\"---a-pie-chart\" style=\"position:relative;\">. . . a Pie Chart.<a href=\"#---a-pie-chart\" aria-label=\"   a pie chart permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>Pie charts are best to use when you are trying to compare parts of a whole. They do not show changes over time.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/piechart\" target=\"_target\" rel=\"external nofollow noreferrer noopener\">More about Pie Chart</a></p>\n<h4 id=\"---a-bar-graph\" style=\"position:relative;\">. . . a Bar Graph.<a href=\"#---a-bar-graph\" aria-label=\"   a bar graph permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>Bar graphs are used to compare things between different groups or to track changes over time. However, bar graphs are best when the changes are larger.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/bar-graph\" target=\"_target\" rel=\"external nofollow noreferrer noopener\">More about Bar Graph</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/distribution-bar\" target=\"_target\" rel=\"external nofollow noreferrer noopener\">More about Distribution bar</a></p>\n<h4 id=\"---an-area-graph\" style=\"position:relative;\">. . . an Area Graph.<a href=\"#---an-area-graph\" aria-label=\"   an area graph permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>Area graphs are very similar to line graphs. They can be used to track changes over time for one or more groups. Use area charts only if you want to show how values develop over time.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/data-visualization/area-graph\">More about Area Graph</a></p>\n<h4 id=\"---an-x-y-plot\" style=\"position:relative;\">. . . an X-Y Plot.<a href=\"#---an-x-y-plot\" aria-label=\"   an x y plot permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>X-Y plots are used to determine relationships between the two different things. The x-axis is used to measure one event (or variable) and the y-axis is used to measure the other. If both variables increase at the same time, they have a positive relationship. If one variable decreases while the other increases, they have a negative relationship. Sometimes the variables don't follow any pattern and have no relationship.</p>\n<p>More about X-Y Plot</p>\n<h4 id=\"---a-map-chart\" style=\"position:relative;\">. . . a Map Chart.<a href=\"#---a-map-chart\" aria-label=\"   a map chart permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>Use a map if you have data with a geographical component. Maps can shade areas in proportion to mapped values, allowing for visual pop-out of high-value areas. Data for map charts must contain geographical names corresponding to the geographical entities represented on the map. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/components/web/data-visualization/map\" target=\"_target\" rel=\"external nofollow noreferrer noopener\">More about Map Chart</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"the-different-parts\" style=\"position:relative;\">The different parts<a href=\"#the-different-parts\" aria-label=\"the different parts permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h3>\n<h4 id=\"legends\" style=\"position:relative;\">Legends<a href=\"#legends\" aria-label=\"legends permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>Important to each graphical element is a legend describing the visual data. The legends should be 16x16 pixels, with text in Arial that describes the legend.</p>\n<p>Position-wise, they should be in close relation to the graph itself. Prefereble on the right or under the graph.</p>\n<h4 id=\"interactivity\" style=\"position:relative;\">Interactivity<a href=\"#interactivity\" aria-label=\"interactivity permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>If the graph/chart has interactivity attached to it. Click on the legends to highlight the different parts in the graph. Even the text of the legend should be clickable.</p>\n<h4 id=\"color\" style=\"position:relative;\">Color<a href=\"#color\" aria-label=\"color permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>LFUI provides a few scales to choose from that will color your visual data according to the visual profile of Länsförsäkringar. The visual identity set a preferable scale of blue or red. Below we have set different set to make it the same for all graphs. Use colors to make your most important value stand out</p>\n<p>We are going to update the colors for better accessibility. [2019-12-01]</p>\n<p>Here are the latest sets of colors to use:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Blue colors - 10 colors</li>\n<li>Red colors - 10 colors</li>\n<li>Blue to red - 16 colors</li>\n<li>Red to blue - 16 colors</li>\n<li>Hybrid - 4 colors</li>\n<li>Map - 15 colors</li>\n<li>Disabled / not selected / inactive color is grey #d9d9d9 (smoke).</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"accessibility\" style=\"position:relative;\">Accessibility<a href=\"#accessibility\" aria-label=\"accessibility permalink\" class=\"Heading--anchor after\"><svg width=\"14\" height=\"19\"><path d=\"M2.965 18.293l1.02-4.992h3.68l-1.009 4.992h1.758l1.02-4.992h3.609v-1.746H9.785l.88-4.254h2.378V5.555h-2.027l1.02-5.028h-1.77l-1.02 5.028H5.555L6.575.527H4.815l-1.02 5.028H.247V7.3h3.2l-.868 4.254H.246V13.3h1.98l-1.019 4.992h1.758zm5.05-6.738h-3.68L5.204 7.3h3.692l-.88 4.254z\" fill=\"#E5E5E5\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\"/></svg></a></h4>\n<p>Charts, graphs and maps use visuals to convey complex images to users. But since they are images, these media provide serious accessibility issues to colorblind users and users of screen readers. </p>\n<p>Generally speaking an ALT tag cannot do justice to a complex chart. One way to describe a chart is to provide both a text summary and a properly coded data table near the chart.</p>\n<p>This serves multiple audiences because a chart can show trends, but a table can provide exact data for those who are interested.</p>"}},"pageContext":{"id":"1aa8b4ab-e5d9-55f6-bd71-77b0963eff45"}}}